alize.\r\n\r\nA pull request is in the works.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>The ServerFixture::Load(world, paused) function (which is used for regression testing) returns before the world has been fully initialized. In <a href=\"#!/osrf/gazebo/commits/806ed4e\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">806ed4e</a>, I've added a test to the <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/osrf/gazebo/compare/test_server_fixture_load_paused..default\" rel=\"nofollow\">test_server_fixture_load_paused branch</a> to illustrate the problem. On my machine, the world requires more than 100 ms but less than 1000 ms to initialize.</p>\n<p>A pull request is in the works.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c-aa76-4fab35448816"}, "state": "closed", "version": {"name": "all", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/versions/225575.json"}}}, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2013-01-02T18:41:45.873753+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2016-09-14T19:44:43.419125+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 334}